To characterize the helicity-dependent photoresponse of our device we tune the polarization of the incident light by a λ/4 waveplate. Over a 360° waveplate rotation, the light is modulated twice between left and right circular polarization. Figure 1d shows the helicity-dependent photocurrent IPC as a function of the angle θ of the fast axis of the waveplate with respect to the polarization axis of the incoming laser. The resulting signal IPC(θ) can be phenomenologically described as1IPCθ=I0+Csin2θ+Lsin4θ+δ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
